API_Description: Exports a custom dictionary to a new file that was opened using the spell methods `customDictionaryOpen` or `customDictionaryCreate` .

cName.description: The dictionary name used when this dictionary was opened or created.

Returns: `true` if successful, `false` on failure. This method will fail if the user does not have sufficient file system permission.
Examples:
Export a custom dictionary, which can then be sent to other users. (See the example that follows customDictionaryCreate .)

```
spell.customDictionaryExport("JavaScript");
```
